          a
          
            i
            +
            j
          
        
        .
      
    
    {\displaystyle \sum _{n=0}^{\infty }{\frac {u^{n}}{n!}}\Delta ^{n}a_{i}=e^{-u}\sum _{j=0}^{\infty }{\frac {u^{j}}{j!}}a_{i+j}.}
  So in particular,

  
    
      
        f
        (
        a
        +
        t
        )
        =
        
          lim
          
            h
            →
            
              0
              
                +
              
            
          
        
        
          e
          
